+ * Fix (this check): store a small content FINGERPRINT alongside each cache
+ * entry at add-time (a cheap hash over a couple of STABLE header bytes at
+ * the key address -- [0,6) and [8,16), deliberately skipping ANIMDATA's
+ * own useNum field at [6,8), which legitimately changes across repeat
+ * lookups of a genuinely still-valid self-registered entry). On a hit,
+ * recompute the SAME fingerprint over what's actually at that address
+ * RIGHT NOW; a mismatch means the bytes underneath changed since this
+ * entry was added -- i.e. the address was reclaimed and reused without
+ * ever going through mp6_animCacheRemove -- so treat it as a MISS (clear
+ * the stale slot, keep scanning, fall through to a fresh, correct parse)
+ * instead of trusting a pointer match against memory that may no longer
+ * hold what it once did.
